### Describe the bug

When generating [ProblemDetails](url) using [IProblemDetailsService](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/c2ea7d85fd7d6d0a534583ba508fed7e85d81b63/src/Http/Http.Abstractions/src/ProblemDetails/IProblemDetailsService.cs#L10) the default [IProblemDetailsWriter](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/c2ea7d85fd7d6d0a534583ba508fed7e85d81b63/src/Http/Http.Abstractions/src/ProblemDetails/IProblemDetailsWriter.cs) does not honor JsonOptions. 

Response JSON become mixed, example below. Some properties are honoring but default properties use lower casing naming policy. 

RFC9110 does not specify naming policy, framework can therefor configure own behaviour.

```json
{
  "type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc9110#section-15.6.1",
  "title": "An unhandled exception occurred.",
  "status": 500,
  "instance": "GET /exception/",
  "TRACE_ID": "00-d34fce0b88ea8ece526e91f66fd88cc2-2272e225585276ab-00"
}
```

### Expected Behavior

 Either:

1. Response JSON honor stack configured JsonOptions across whole ProblemDetail response 
 ..or...
2. Response JSON do not honor stack configured JsonOptions across whole ProblemDetail response

### Steps To Reproduce

```csharp
// configure naming policy for UPPER_CASE

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
builder.Services.AddProblemDetails();

builder.Services.ConfigureHttpJsonOptions(options =>
{
    options.SerializerOptions.PropertyNamingPolicy = System.Text.Json.JsonNamingPolicy.SnakeCaseUpper;
});
builder.Services.Configure<Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Json.JsonOptions>(
    options =>
    {
        options.SerializerOptions.PropertyNamingPolicy = System.Text.Json.JsonNamingPolicy.SnakeCaseUpper;
    });

var app = builder.Build();
app.MapGet("/exception/", () => { throw new Exception("This is an unhandled exception"); });
await app.RunAsync();
```

Response has mixed json naming syntax:

```json
{
  "type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc9110#section-15.6.1",
  "title": "An unhandled exception occurred.",
  "status": 500,
  "detail": "An unhandled error occured. Staff have been notified. Please use the traceId for reference.",
  "instance": "GET /exception/",
  "TRACE_ID": "00-d34fce0b88ea8ece526e91f66fd88cc2-2272e225585276ab-00"
}
```

